---
---

<div class="section-container">
  <div class="open-roles-section">
    <h2 class="sub-heading">Open roles</h2>
    <p class="roles-intro">
      We are looking for purpose-driven individuals for the following roles.
    </p>

    <div class="roles-grid">

      <!-- Legal & Compliance Officer -->
      <article class="role-card" data-role="legal-compliance-officer">
        <header class="role-card__head">
          <div class="role-card__title-block">
            <h3 class="role-title">Legal &amp; Compliance Officer</h3>
            <div class="role-badges" role="list">
              <span class="role-badge" role="listitem">1 opening</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">1 year</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">5 hours / week</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </header>

        <p class="role-lead">
          Help ensure our nonprofit operates ethically, transparently, and in full compliance with Nepal's legal and regulatory environment.
        </p>

        <div class="role-content">
          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="legal-do-heading">
            <h4 id="legal-do-heading" class="role-panel__title">What you&rsquo;ll do</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Ensure compliance with Company Act (OCR) and SWC regulations, including registrations, filings, and reporting.</li>
              <li>Manage and maintain a dual compliance calendar (OCR filings, SWC reporting, donor requirements).</li>
              <li>Draft, review, and manage agreements (MoUs, partnerships, contracts).</li>
              <li>Lead and support the Annual General Meeting (AGM), including documentation, board coordination, and regulatory compliance.</li>
              <li>Support audit processes by organizing documentation and coordinating with auditors (financial + compliance aspects).</li>
              <li>Develop and maintain key organizational policies (governance, finance, HR, data/privacy, conflict of interest).</li>
              <li>Ensure compliance with donor requirements and project approvals (via SWC where applicable).</li>
              <li>Advise the team on legal risks, governance practices, and ethical decision-making.</li>
              <li>Strengthen transparency and accountability across programs, partnerships, and operations.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="legal-look-heading">
            <h4 id="legal-look-heading" class="role-panel__title">What we&rsquo;re looking for</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Background in law, compliance, public policy, or a related field.</li>
              <li>Previous experience in legal/compliance roles is preferred, especially in NGOs, nonprofit structures.</li>
              <li>Understanding of Nepal's Company Act and SWC regulations.</li>
              <li>Familiarity with donor compliance and audit processes is a plus.</li>
              <li>Strong organizational, documentation, and policy-writing skills.</li>
              <li>Ability to simplify legal concepts for non-legal team members.</li>
              <li>Proactive, detail-oriented, and trustworthy.</li>
              <li>Interest in climate, youth, or social impact.</li>
              <li>Bonus: experience working with INGOs, grants, or multi-stakeholder partnerships.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
        </div>

        <footer class="role-card__foot">
          <a
            href="https://forms.gle/P2VEUBQMdie3rgp56"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="apply-button apply-button--wide"
            aria-label="Apply for Legal & Compliance Officer role"
          >
            Apply for this role
          </a>
          <p class="role-footnote">
            Questions? Email <a href="mailto:info@nepalclimatehub.org">info@nepalclimatehub.org</a>
          </p>
        </footer>
      </article>

      <!-- Climate Communicator (Writer) -->
      <article class="role-card" data-role="climate-communicator">
        <header class="role-card__head">
          <div class="role-card__title-block">
            <h3 class="role-title">Climate Communicator (Writer)</h3>
            <div class="role-badges" role="list">
              <span class="role-badge" role="listitem">2 openings</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">6 months</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">7 hours / week</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </header>

        <p class="role-lead">
          Help make climate change understandable, relatable, and engaging for youth and the wider public by translating complex ideas into clear, accessible content, so we can educate, inspire, and empower meaningful climate action.
        </p>

        <div class="role-content">
          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="comm-do-heading">
            <h4 id="comm-do-heading" class="role-panel__title">What you&rsquo;ll do</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Write clear, engaging, and easy-to-understand content on climate topics for diverse audiences.</li>
              <li>Break down complex concepts such as climate justice, loss and damage, climate finance, mitigation, and adaptation into relatable narratives.</li>
              <li>Create content that highlights local and global climate issues, including the perspectives of indigenous and vulnerable communities.</li>
              <li>Develop blogs, articles, social media posts, and educational materials aligned with Nepal Climate Hub's mission.</li>
              <li>Research climate topics and ensure accuracy while keeping content simple and impactful.</li>
              <li>Collaborate with the team to align content with campaigns, programs, and outreach activities.</li>
              <li>Use storytelling techniques to connect climate issues with everyday life and youth experiences.</li>
              <li>Continuously experiment with formats and styles to improve engagement and reach.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="comm-look-heading">
            <h4 id="comm-look-heading" class="role-panel__title">What we&rsquo;re looking for</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Strong writing and storytelling skills with the ability to simplify complex ideas.</li>
              <li>Interest in climate change, sustainability, and social impact.</li>
              <li>Ability to communicate in a clear, engaging, and audience-friendly tone.</li>
              <li>Basic research skills and attention to accuracy and credibility.</li>
              <li>Creative mindset with the ability to connect global climate issues to local contexts.</li>
              <li>Self-motivated, consistent, and open to feedback.</li>
              <li>Experience in content writing, blogging, or communication is a plus (but not required).</li>
              <li>Bonus: experience or strong interest in climate advocacy, campaigning, social media engagement, or working with youth-focused initiatives.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
        </div>

        <footer class="role-card__foot">
          <a
            href="https://forms.gle/P2VEUBQMdie3rgp56"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="apply-button apply-button--wide"
            aria-label="Apply for Climate Communicator (Writer) role"
          >
            Apply for this role
          </a>
          <p class="role-footnote">
            Questions? Email <a href="mailto:info@nepalclimatehub.org">info@nepalclimatehub.org</a>
          </p>
        </footer>
      </article>

      <!-- Indigenous Climate Storyteller -->
      <article class="role-card" data-role="indigenous-climate-storyteller">
        <header class="role-card__head">
          <div class="role-card__title-block">
            <h3 class="role-title">Indigenous Climate Storyteller</h3>
            <div class="role-badges" role="list">
              <span class="role-badge" role="listitem">1 opening</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">6 months</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">7 hours / week</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </header>

        <p class="role-lead">
          Help center indigenous voices in climate conversations by documenting, sharing, and amplifying the knowledge, lived experiences, and stories of indigenous communities.
        </p>

        <div class="role-content">
          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="indigenous-do-heading">
            <h4 id="indigenous-do-heading" class="role-panel__title">What you&rsquo;ll do</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Document and share stories, knowledge systems, and lived experiences of indigenous communities in relation to climate change.</li>
              <li>Highlight key issues such as traditional ecological knowledge, climate impacts, resilience, and adaptation practices.</li>
              <li>Write and develop content (articles, narratives, profiles, campaigns) that authentically represent indigenous voices.</li>
              <li>Work closely with the design and social media team to transform stories into engaging, impactful content formats.</li>
              <li>Build relationships and coordinate with indigenous communities to ensure ethical, respectful, and accurate storytelling.</li>
              <li>Ensure stories are shared in a way that empowers communities and avoids misrepresentation or exploitation.</li>
              <li>Contribute to campaigns and initiatives that amplify indigenous perspectives in climate discourse.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="indigenous-look-heading">
            <h4 id="indigenous-look-heading" class="role-panel__title">What we&rsquo;re looking for</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Strong interest or lived connection to indigenous communities and their knowledge systems.</li>
              <li>Candidates from indigenous communities are strongly preferred to ensure authenticity and lived perspective.</li>
              <li>Experience or interest in storytelling, writing, documentation, or community engagement.</li>
              <li>Understanding of climate change issues, especially how they impact indigenous communities.</li>
              <li>Ability to communicate stories with sensitivity, respect, and cultural awareness.</li>
              <li>Strong collaboration skills to work with design and social media teams.</li>
              <li>Self-driven, empathetic, and committed to ethical storytelling.</li>
              <li>Bonus: prior experience in advocacy, community work, storytelling, or writing related to indigenous rights, climate justice, or social impact.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
        </div>

        <footer class="role-card__foot">
          <a
            href="https://forms.gle/P2VEUBQMdie3rgp56"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="apply-button apply-button--wide"
            aria-label="Apply for Indigenous Climate Storyteller role"
          >
            Apply for this role
          </a>
          <p class="role-footnote">
            Questions? Email <a href="mailto:info@nepalclimatehub.org">info@nepalclimatehub.org</a>
          </p>
        </footer>
      </article>

      <!-- UI/UX Designer -->
      <article class="role-card" data-role="ui-ux-designer">
        <header class="role-card__head">
          <div class="role-card__title-block">
            <h3 class="role-title">UI/UX Designer</h3>
            <div class="role-badges" role="list">
              <span class="role-badge" role="listitem">2 openings</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">3–6 months</span>
              <span class="role-badge role-badge--muted" role="listitem">7 hours / week</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </header>

        <p class="role-lead">
          Help us craft intuitive, accessible interfaces for our platform and campaigns—so climate information feels clear, engaging, and actionable for young people in Nepal and beyond.
        </p>

        <div class="role-content">
          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="uiux-do-heading">
            <h4 id="uiux-do-heading" class="role-panel__title">What you&rsquo;ll do</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Design user-friendly flows and screens for web (and mobile where relevant).</li>
              <li>Create wireframes, mockups, and prototypes—usually in Figma or similar.</li>
              <li>Partner with content, storytelling, and engineering so designs ship smoothly.</li>
              <li>Use design to make climate topics easier to understand and act on.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="role-panel" aria-labelledby="uiux-look-heading">
            <h4 id="uiux-look-heading" class="role-panel__title">What we&rsquo;re looking for</h4>
            <ul class="role-list">
              <li>Comfort with a modern design tool (e.g. Figma, Adobe XD).</li>
              <li>User-centered thinking: clarity, hierarchy, and accessibility.</li>
              <li>Collaboration, feedback, and attention to detail.</li>
              <li>Interest in climate, youth, or social impact (no need to be an expert).</li>
              <li>Bonus: experience with design systems or component libraries.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
        </div>

        <footer class="role-card__foot">
          <a
            href="https://forms.gle/P2VEUBQMdie3rgp56"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="apply-button apply-button--wide"
            aria-label="Apply for UI/UX Designer role"
          >
            Apply for this role
          </a>
          <p class="role-footnote">
            Questions? Email <a href="mailto:info@nepalclimatehub.org">info@nepalclimatehub.org</a>
          </p>
        </footer>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .section-container {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    margin-bottom: 120px;
  }

  .open-roles-section {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .sub-heading {
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.5vw, 28px);
    line-height: 1.25;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    color: #1a1b1e;
  }

  .roles-intro {
    max-width: none;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    color: #4b5563;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .roles-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .role-card {
    width: 100%;
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid #e8eaed;
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 28px) clamp(20px, 3vw, 32px);
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 2px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04),
      0 4px 16px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.05);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    transition:
      box-shadow 0.25s ease,
      border-color 0.25s ease;
  }

  .role-card:hover {
    border-color: #d4e85a;
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 2px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.06),
      0 8px 24px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
  }

  .role-card__head {
    padding-bottom: 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #f1f3f5;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .role-card__title-block {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px 16px;
  }

  .role-title {
    font-size: clamp(18px, 2vw, 22px);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a1b1e;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .role-badges {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .role-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1;
    padding: 5px 12px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #cefe00;
    color: #1a1b1e;
  }

  .role-badge--muted {
    background: #f1f3f5;
    color: #495057;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .role-lead {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #495057;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  .role-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(12px, 2vw, 20px);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .role-card__foot {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid #f1f3f5;
  }

  .role-panel {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    border: 1px solid #eef0f2;
  }

  .role-panel__title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a1b1e;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .role-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
  }

  .role-list li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #374151;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .role-list li:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .role-list li::marker {
    color: #364fc7;
  }

  .apply-button:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid #364fc7;
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .apply-button:active {
    transform: scale(0.99);
  }

  .apply-button--wide {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: 12px 20px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-decoration: none;
    background: #cefe00;
    color: #1a1b1e;
    transition:
      background 0.2s ease,
      transform 0.15s ease;
  }

  .apply-button--wide:hover {
    background: #b8e600;
    color: #1a1b1e;
  }

  .role-footnote {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #6b7280;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .role-footnote a {
    color: #364fc7;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .role-footnote a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 1280px) {
    .section-container {
      padding: 40px 48px;
      margin-bottom: 50px;
    }
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
    .section-container {
      padding: 20px 24px;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }

    .role-content {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .role-card__title-block {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 8px;
    }
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 480px) {
    .role-card {
      padding: 18px 16px;
      border-radius: 16px;
    }

    .role-panel {
      padding: 14px;
    }
  }
</style>
